headline: Alaska Air Places Record 110-Jet Order With Boeing to Expand International Reach
summary: The airline ordered 737 Max 10s and 787-10s, extending deliveries through 2035 after acquiring Hawaiian Airlines.

headline: United Airlines price target raised to $153 from $132 at Citi
summary: Citi analyst John Godyn raised the firm’s price target on United Airlines (UAL) to $153 from $132 and keeps a Buy rating on the shares. The firm updated targets in the airlines group as part of a Q4 earnings preview. Citi’s business travel barometer has bottomed, the analyst tells investors in a research note.
